You are doing it the right way. I've installed tons of torrent games, where many are skidrow versions without any infection. Like you, I've stayed away from this one after observing in- and outbound connections to ip of webhost in a sandboxed environment, which resolved to a webserver with controlpanel for botnets...
I've de-assembled the dll's and the instructions are hardcoded in each to connect to the same ip to accepts commands from a host.

What I did to get it working with the mini-image:
1) Mount the game;
2) Used xxxx's as serial;
3) Installing the game (it will take a while);
4) Uninstalled GFWL from my pc;
5) Installed GFWL FROM THE IMAGE (v3.5.88.0 (in controlpanel));
6) Downloaded and mounted the mini-image from Gamecopyworld;
7) Started the game;
8) Made an offline account;
9) Made playername;
10) Enjoyed the game with savefeature, even after 2 days of gameplay without any infection :-)

Good luck. If it doesn't work, please tell me. I'll keep a close eye to the comments.

